    • Method Detail

      • solve

        public java.util.List solve(java.util.Vector numbers,
                            int k,
                            double p)
        the method solves the number clustering problem and returns a List<Integer> result where result[i] indicates to which cluster from [1...k] the numbers[i] element belongs to. Last element of result vector is value of partition obtained. If the problem is infeasible, null is returned.
        Parameters:
        numbers - Vector<Double> not necessarily sorted, size let's say n
        k - int
        p - double
        Returns:
        List<Integer>, size n+1, last element is Double, the value of the partition
